SIMPLE: recto
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recto-
<hw>Rec"to-</hw> <pr>(r?k"t?*)</pr>. <def>A combining form indicating
<xex>connection with</xex>, or <xex>relation to</xex>, <xex>the
rectum</xex>; <as>as, <ex>recto</ex>-vesical</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recto</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Recto
<hw>Rec"to</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Abbrev. fr. LL. breve de
<ets>recto</ets>. See <er>Right</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A
writ of right.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recto</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Recto
<hw>Rec"to</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>recto</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>The right-hand page; -- opposed to
<xex>verso</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rector</ent>⟦br⟧
